ACE="Verdana,Arial">Solo Spectre in Ferrott.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Over that last couple of days I have been seeing many a necromancer at the solo Spectre spot in Ferrott. Not an unusual sight. What is unusual to me is the fact that these necromancers are actually using PETS to do the solo Spectre! This REALLY suprises me as I have been doing the solo Spectre without a pet since about level 36. I will let you all in on how to do this.<br>
<br>
Basically, if you follow these steps you will maximize your experience. You will take down the Spectres faster, thus getting more Spectres per hour. Rumors or not, I like hunting without the pet if I can. Seems to me like I get more experience per kill then with him. Might be an illusion or it might be true.<br>
<br>
Anyhow here goes.<br>
<br>
You will be needing these spells in your arsenal.<br>
<br>
Expel/SoP<br>
VoS<br>
Tap<br>
Engulfing Darkness<br>
Dooming Darkness<br>
Panic the Dead<br>
CoB<br>
Feign<br>
<br>
Start off on the top of the hill facing the Spectre. Cast Dooming. After you cast (whether it is resisted or not) turn about face and run to the other end of the hill. If Dooming stuck then use Tap (if low on health) or Expel. If Dooming didn't stick hit it with Engulfing (lower cast time). Run to the bottom of the hill near the small tree and Panic the Dead until it sticks. Next apply VoS (gotta get this off because he will be headed back to the Spectre cave). Once it sticks he will turn around. Then just keep nailing him with Expel and Tap if you get low on health.<br>
<br>
If it is done right, the Spectre should be dead before he even makes it down the hill.<br>
<br>
Of course you'll need to keep Darkness and Fear applied. The Spectre SHOULD be dead even before Fear or Darkness breaks.<br>
<br>
Hope this tactic will help you experience bar move a little faster. Remember, this gets easier as you go up in level as well.<br>
<br>
Once you hit the 40 mark, in my opinion, you should only do this spot if you are waiting for a group in L Guk or somewhere of the sorts. We can make MUCH better exp after 40 in Kunark or in a dungeon.<br>
